(28, 12, 'upgradingHomeNetwork', '<div style="all: unset;width: 100%;"><h2><strong>Upgrading Home Network</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Home networking was never as easy as connecting one device to another. This particular guide would walk over the verbiage of setting up a home network. When it comes to upgrading your home network, you have a lot of things to learn about.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>What Do You Require from Your Network?</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Prior to whipping out your credit card or getting dollars in your pocket to buy a gear, you have to find out what you are trying to achieve with your home network. Are you looking to connect to two or more laptops or perhaps a Wi-Fi equipped mobile phone to the web for internet access? You may be capable of getting by with just one access point. Are you working every day at home and you need internet access to the corporate network via VPN technology? You would need to use a good router which can manage the passing through of virtual private network.</p>\r\n<p>Are you a sincere online gamer? Do you need to get connected to more multiplayer games online or through some services Xbox Live on a regular basis? You would need to not just buy an efficient router but likewise, you have to sheer yourself on major functionalities and capabilities like port forwarding. Are you watching the television through the web and with the use of devices such as Hulu and websites that are owned by the network?</p>\r\n<p>When you are streaming videos from the web using different locations inside your home, you may want to use a dependable networking infrastructure and that probably is a cabled network. Finding out the answers to these questions would definitely go far towards making sure that you have the network that is 100% suitable for your home without having to spend too much within the process.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Entrust Your Needs to Us</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Our team consists of highly experienced professionals who have years of experience in the i